<!-- Hora ::: Start -->
<div class="row">
<div class="col-xs-12">
<h5><b>Hora</b></h5>
</div><!--/.col-xs-12 -->
</div><!--/.row -->
<div class="row">
<div class="col-xs-6">
 <div>
  Duration of a day is Sun-rise to Sun-rise. This period is divided into 24 equal parts and they are called <i>Horas</i>.
  A hora is almost equal to an hour and these horas are ruled by different planets.
 </div>
 <div class="list-group">
 <div class="list-group-item">
  <div align="center"><b>Find the lord of the Hora at 9:40 PM on Wednesday<br/> when Sun-rise is 6:10 AM</b></div>
  <div class="mtop15p">
    <ol>
	  <li><b>Find the Difference:</b> 21:40 - 6:10 = 15:30 (16th hour is running)</li>
	  <li>Lord at Sunrise on Wedneday is Mercury.</li>
	  <li><b>Find 16th hour lord:</b> 16%7 = 2 (2nd Planet from Mercury = Moon)</li>
	</ol>
  </div>
 </div><!--/.list-group-item -->
 </div><!--/.list-group -->
</div><!--/.col-xs-6 -->
<div class="col-xs-6">
<!-- -->
<div class="list-group">
<div class="list-group-item">
 <div align="center"><b>First Hora of the Day</b></div>
 <div>It is ruled by the lord of the Weekday.</div>
 <div class="row">
   <div class="col-xs-3"><b>Sunday:</b></div><div class="col-xs-3">Sun</div>
   <div class="col-xs-3"><b>Thursday:</b></div><div class="col-xs-3">Jupiter</div>
 </div>
 <div class="row">
   <div class="col-xs-3"><b>Monday:</b></div><div class="col-xs-3">Moon</div>
   <div class="col-xs-3"><b>Friday:</b></div><div class="col-xs-3">Venus</div>
 </div>
 <div class="row">
   <div class="col-xs-3"><b>Tuesday:</b></div><div class="col-xs-3">Mars</div>
   <div class="col-xs-3"><b>Saturday:</b></div><div class="col-xs-3">Saturn</div>
 </div>
 <div class="row">
   <div class="col-xs-3"><b>Wednesday:</b></div><div class="col-xs-3">Mercury</div>
 </div>
 <div>Next Horas are ruled by lords in following order format</div>
</div><!--/.list-group-item -->
